WEBVTT Offset: 0;

00:19.888 --> 00:21.910
"if we were back"

00:21.910 --> 00:24.607
"way in the past"

00:24.607 --> 00:28.315
"what would that make you?"

00:28.989 --> 00:31.685
"between only us"

00:31.685 --> 00:33.708
"the stars above"

00:33.708 --> 00:37.753
"and you right there"

00:38.764 --> 00:41.966
"we've all changed a lot"

00:41.966 --> 00:43.820
"strayed a lot"

00:43.820 --> 00:48.202
"but there's still no clue"

00:48.202 --> 00:56.629
"about what it is we were meant to be"

00:57.640 --> 01:00.000
walking through halls

01:00.000 --> 01:06.067
dressed in all fonts titling each of you

01:07.079 --> 01:09.101
but even so

01:09.101 --> 01:16.517
your reality is only kept inside

01:16.517 --> 01:19.551
not much longer now

01:19.551 --> 01:25.955
I promise that youll be there someday

01:25.955 --> 01:35.730
known in that world as you were always meant to be

01:36.404 --> 01:38.933
for everyone who was looking through this window

01:38.933 --> 01:42.472
perhaps this is the first time that we were seen this way

01:42.472 --> 01:45.169
the realest way

01:45.169 --> 01:47.528
watching eye to eye

01:47.528 --> 01:49.551
from the sun's fall, to rise

01:49.551 --> 01:54.944
we always knew things would change

01:54.944 --> 01:58.989
again

01:59.326 --> 02:04.045
there's so much that I still have yet to know

02:04.045 --> 02:08.764
and I still have no clue where I should go

02:08.764 --> 02:13.146
with a future that's left in my hands

02:13.146 --> 02:18.876
I still turn around and see you waving there

02:18.876 --> 02:22.921
words, all scattered throughout the sky
(no matter the lens you see through)

02:22.921 --> 02:25.955
one so blue, perhaps it all might be fine
(no matter the lens you see through)

02:25.955 --> 02:27.640
one so blue, perhaps it all might be fine
(like always, I'll be here for you)

02:27.640 --> 02:30.674
but for now that time has faced us again
(like always, I'll be here for you)

02:30.674 --> 02:31.685
but for now that time has faced us again
(from a screen to an eye)

02:31.685 --> 02:33.371
to say farewell
(from a screen to an eye)

02:33.371 --> 02:36.404
to say farewell

02:36.404 --> 02:41.461
(it's in your hands)

02:41.461 --> 02:44.157
(I'll say it again)
